<methods><methodStep><description><section><title>Methods</title>
<para>We studied insect pollinator activity on flowers of 29 species of trees and shrubs in the Skukuza Ranger District, Kruger National Park, Mpumalanga Province, Republic of South Africa, during the late dry season and/or early rainy seasons in the years 2009-2012 (inclusive).  Floral visitor sampling was conducted under optimal temperature (greater than 20&#176; C) and precipitation (non-rainy, usually clear skies to partly cloudy) conditions for insect activity.  We recorded lists of pollinator species observed on each plant species for further food web analysis.</para>
</section>
</description>
</methodStep>
